{
  "texts": [
    "The investigation scrutinizes the characteristics of these studies, such as their research aims, stimuli, and interview strategies.",
    "It examines the interplay among these elements, including variations in the purposes of SR employment across disciplines.",
    "The ultimate goal of our study is to provide valuable insights for future applications of SR in education and also to aid researchers in exploring the external behaviors and internal thought processes of both instructors and students in a more effective manner.",
    "The theoretical foundation of SR in education.",
    "SR is a research technique inspired by Dewey's (1933) reflective thinking concept, which involves presenting participants with vivid prompts to evoke their memories of an original scenario (Bloom, 1953)."
  ]
}